summary:
Battle Hardened Warpaints

As it was believed that certain symbols offered protection and guidance,
nearly all ancient cultures began to dress their warriors in such markings...

[center][/center][center][/center][center][/center][center][/center][center][/center][center][/center][center][color=#E42217][size=5][b][i]Version 2 is now added! It consists of sets 3 & 4![/i][/b][/size][b][i]
[size=6]The Standalone version is now available as well! v2.5!!
YES! All of the warpaints can now be accessed through RACE MENU!![/size][/i][/b][/color][/center]
[center][/center][center]﻿[/center][center]﻿[url=http://s1340.photobucket.com/user/Diethardt/media/9b448350-7304-4cb4-8405-98561b281cf0_zpslglhvgba.png.html][img]http://i1340.photobucket.com/albums/o723/Diethardt/9b448350-7304-4cb4-8405-98561b281cf0_zpslglhvgba.png~original[/img][/url][/center]
[center][/center]
[center][color=#E42217][size=4]Simply open the .rar file, drag and drop the Data file into your Skyrim folder and overwrite if needed. You can also copy and paste the single file you wish to use in the Tintmasks folder. (Data/texture/actors/character/character assets/tintmasks).[/size][/color][/center]

[center][color=#E42217][size=4]If you don't want to replace the specific warpaint number I have saved, chose the number you want to replace and after the underscore ( _ ) change the number to the one you want to use (01-10).[/size][/color][/center]

[center][color=#E42217][size=4]You can now mix and match between the 4 sets for even more combinations![/size][/color][/center]
[center][url=http://s1340.photobucket.com/user/Diethardt/media/e4db5139-a57a-421c-a82d-a3c7f1489ac8_zpsvusrcx0a.png.html][img]http://i1340.photobucket.com/albums/o723/Diethardt/e4db5139-a57a-421c-a82d-a3c7f1489ac8_zpsvusrcx0a.png~original[/img][/url][/center]
[center][color=#E42217][size=4]Delete the files in the Tintmasks folder to return to the vanilla warpaint or overwrite with your own or other warpaints if you so choose.[/size][/color][/center]
[center][img]http://i1340.photobucket.com/albums/o723/Diethardt/f50abca6-c033-44ee-8824-17afc850a545_zps2c8rpgxw.png~original[/img][/center]
[center][color=#E42217][size=4]Using [url=http://skyrim.nexusmods.com/mods/29624/][b]RACE MENU[/b][/url] by (url=https://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/users/2950481)[b]Expired[/b](/url) will help tremendously with utilizing the layering of these warpaints. It is not necessary, but it is HIGHLY RECOMMENDED! They will NOT look like they do in the screenshots otherwise.[/size][/color][/center]

[center][size=6][color=#E42217][font=Nueva Std][i][u][b]FOR THE WARPAINTS TO LOOK LIKE THEY DO IN THE IMAGES[/b][/u][/i]:[/font][/color][/size][/center]

[center][color=#E42217][size=4]You should use [url=http://skse.silverlock.org/]SKSE 1.7.3[/url]; Thanks to a [u][b].ini[/b][/u] setting added to [i]SKSE[/i], it is now possible to use HD 2048x2048
(up to 4096x4096) warpaint applied to your character rather than being limited to the vanilla resolution (256x256). To allow this you [u][b]MUST[/b][/u] have [i]SKSE[/i] installed and you should add these lines to your [i]SKSE.ini[/i]:[/size][/color][/center]

[size=4][color=#000000][b][Display]
iTintTextureResolution=2048         [/b][/color][/size][font=Times New Roman][size=4][color=#000000][size=4][color=#000000](or 4096 if you prefer)
[/color][/size][/color][/size][/font]

[center][color=#E42217][size=4][u]Note[/u]: Prior to the introduction of this SKSE settings, no matter how big the textures were, the game downscaled them to the vanilla resolution at 256 x 256. This setting though, while allowing for higher resolution warpaints, will cause low resolution textures to look worse due to upscaling.[/size][/color][/center]

[center][color=#E42217][size=4]Because these are done in Hi Def 2048 x 2048, if you do not use this SKSE tweak, the warpaints will look more pixelated than in my images.[/size][/color][/center]

[center][color=#E42217][size=4]I will also be including the Modder's Resource versions for those of you who do not use SKSE, it will be at the default resolution of 256 x 256 and will work with the Creation Kit.[/size][/color][/center]

[center][color=#E42217][size=4]Also, I will include a folder in the options section, which will include the much needed SKSE.ini tweak![/size][/color][/center]
[center][url=http://s1340.photobucket.com/user/Diethardt/media/9222dbe7-c285-49e3-92d0-5fd1f0a6e68c_zpsfa9mlv68.png.html][img]http://i1340.photobucket.com/albums/o723/Diethardt/9222dbe7-c285-49e3-92d0-5fd1f0a6e68c_zpsfa9mlv68.png~original[/img][/url][/center]
[center][color=#E42217][size=4]The assets from this file may not be used without either mine or netherwalks expressed permission. Please feel free to ask, as we will most likely approve. Thank you for your respect regarding this.[/size][/color][/center]
[center][img]http://i1340.photobucket.com/albums/o723/Diethardt/b1d55041-dfe8-4454-8e63-b94b8c260b37_zpsyryempbp.png~original[/img][/center]
[center][color=#E42217][size=5][b]HUGE THANKS[/b][/size][size=4] to Every One of our friends for helping test out and promote our warpaint collection![/size][/color][/center]
